Description: Shiny application (GExPipe) for high-throughput genomic analysis of bulk RNA-seq and
    microarray data (e.g. from GEO). Integrates with Bioconductor (GEOquery, Biobase,
    limma, DESeq2, edgeR, clusterProfiler) for a single workflow: download, QC,
    normalization, batch correction, differential expression, WGCNA, pathway enrichment,
    PPI, and machine learning. Uses common data structures
    (ExpressionSet, DGEList) for interoperability. For a full dependency tree (including
    STRINGdb + PPI helpers), use BiocManager::install("GExPipe", dependencies = TRUE).
    STRING data are downloaded on first PPI use (internet required); they cannot be bundled in the package.
